-- HSBC's de Silva Moves to Head Asia-Pacific Rates Research in Hong Kong
-- Anchalee Worrachate
-- 2010-07-30T09:41:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/hsbc-s-de-silva-moves-to-head-asia-pacific-rates-research-in-hong-kong.html

          
          
             HSBC Holdings Plc, Europe’s biggest
bank by market value, appointed  Andre de Silva  as its head of
Asia-Pacific rates research, according to a company memo.  
 De Silva, who relocated to Hong Kong from London where he
was deputy head of global fixed-income strategy at the bank,
started his new job this month. His move to Asia “will
facilitate further integration of our global product and
strengthen our position in the region,” the company said in the
memo obtained by Bloomberg News today.  
 He will report to  Steven Major , global head of fixed-income
research, and to  Dilip Shahani , head of global research Asia
Pacific.  
